### Refined Proposal

The refined proposal focuses on developing a **PAC-Bayes spectral stability framework for latency-aware inference systems**. The key idea is to leverage PAC-Bayes theory to derive spectral stability bounds that can be used to design and optimize inference systems with strict latency constraints. This approach will allow us to provide rigorous guarantees on the stability and performance of latency-aware inference systems, while minimizing computational overhead.

